This article is a transcript of a press conference with Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One. He discusses topics such as the attendees of a speech by the President, the regulation of derivatives, progress on financial reform legislation, the absence of Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac in the reforms, the President's stance on free markets, and potential future legislative priorities such as immigration and energy. He also mentions that the President made phone calls to garner support for immigration reform and that the Department of Interior is responding to the oil rig explosion in Louisiana. The article ends with a clarification that there will not be a value-added tax (VAT).